##Xiantao mask factory in Hubei suspended production four days after resuming work ahead of Spring Festival

Weixin Wangyiqingliu

Features introduction, through the fog, to find the truth. Netease Finance and economics under the original in-depth reporting team, focusing on the survey of listed companies.

Production | Netease Qingliu studio

By Liu Pei, editor in chief | Yan Zhao

Tip Box:

stoolpigeon@service.netease.com

In the intense preparation of the national anti-epidemic war, it is located 100 kilometers southwest of Wuhan ————————————————————————————————————————————————. Hubei Xiantao has advantages in the production of protective clothing and medical masks, Xiaodong Wang, the governor of Hubei Province, said at a regular press conference on Jan. 26 on the prevention and control of the COVID-19 infection.

Xiantao, known as "China's largest base of non-woven fabric" , gathered hundreds of large-scale non-woven fabric production and processing enterprises, exports accounted for nearly one-third of the country. In the first half of 2010, non-woven products accounted for 62 percent of the city's total exports of us $71.92 million, according to the Xiantao government's website, and were the main force supporting Xiantao's export growth from a high base.

The main raw material of the mask is non woven fabric, which makes Xiantao an important place to supply protective materials against COVID-19. However, with the epidemic situation continuing to expand and the market demand for mask resources increasing substantially, and almost "one mask is hard to find, " Netease qingliu learned from several mask manufacturers in Xiantao that in order to strictly investigate fake and inferior mask products, xiantao's watchdog has shut down all civilian mask manufacturers.

And this place, which is reputed to be the largest nonwoven production base in the country and has the natural advantage of mask production, is in an even more complicated predicament: As the focus of the epidemic, in areas where workers are unwilling to go to work, traffic control, many masks business hard to resume work, high demand for raw materials environment, all the civil mask manufacturers closed, making the market circulation of civil masks greatly reduced. The unswitched, medical device manufacturers have their own mask production capacity is lower, more difficult to meet demand, will exacerbate the large gap in the market.

Xiantao shuts down all commercial face masks

On February 1, Wang Yi (not his real name) , the head of a major mask manufacturer in Xiantao, received a phone call from the administration of Industry and commerce informing him that all mask manufacturers without medical device qualifications were closing their doors.

Xiantao mask manufacturers to Netease Qingliu studio confirmed the news.

Xiantao, 100 kilometers west of Wuhan, is also one of the hardest hit areas. It is not only the country's largest non-woven production base, but also the country's important defense supplies.

Therefore, a few days after the Spring Festival, the relevant departments of the Xiantao government began to encourage publicity in the area of non-woven enterprises ready to resume production. Wang Yi is an early resumption of work of a group of mask manufacturers.

Wang Yi they returned to work on the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, to 3-5 times the salary, attract employees to work, overtime production masks. In four days, they produced almost three million masks.

With the increasing demand for mask resources, the price of masks in the market rises, resulting in the emergence of a variety of false masks, or even no "filter material" of the three-no masks.

It was against this background that the Xiantao government shut down all local manufacturers of civilian face masks on February 1. On January 28, members of the Marketing Supervision Administration team led 10 inspection teams to conduct quality and safety inspections of protective products and ensure the normal production of face masks and protective clothing, the bureau's official website reported, more than 300 law enforcement officers were dispatched to conduct a comprehensive inspection of the non-woven fabric enterprises and relevant business units in the city.

On February 2, the Xiantao outbreak command issued a circular. The circular said that market supervision should be strengthened and violations of the law should be strictly investigated and dealt with. Illegal acts discovered through various channels such as inspections, inspections, reports and complaints should be investigated and dealt with promptly and severely, and products involved in cases should be detained in accordance with the law.

But a number of civilian mask manufacturers said, "the government can investigate and deal with fake, but not across-the-board, not because of individual bad business behavior to the entire production of masks are closed. "

Wang Yi said, "The regulatory authorities are now demanding that all non-medical-device-qualified mask manufacturers stop production, ignoring the fact that in the current shortage of masks, the production of civilian masks will lead to a large gap in masks, people can not buy masks, and there are not many medical-device-qualified enterprises in Xiantao, and their production capacity is very low. There will be a significant reduction in mask production capacity".

A number of Xiantao mask manufacturers also told Netease Qingliu that medical mask manufacturers need medical device qualification certificates, while civilian mask manufacturers are not qualified at all, across Xiantao, there are perhaps a dozen or so certified medical devices and face masks, most of which are not. To the medical qualification card neck, equivalent to a large part of the mask production capacity has been cut off.

Xiantao mask maker's struggle to get back to work

However, even if there is no "stop" ahead, Xiantao is far from resuming normal production capacity.

"We are short of raw materials and workers are reluctant to go to work for fear of safety, " said Li Hongyu, director of north China Ruikang Medical Supplies Co. , Ltd. . "Our production capacity is only 1 / 10 of normal. "

North China Ruikang Medical Consumables Co. , Ltd. has the medical production qualification, but has no capacity to achieve the recovery of production capacity.

Several manufacturers said they had stopped production as early as the early Spring Festival. In addition to the difficult staff to return to work, the main raw materials shortage. Because the general end of the year, everyone is in the clearance processing of goods state. If you don't have it in stock by, you won't be able to get it in line after.

Wang Yi's company ordered 30 tons of non-woven materials as early as the Spring Festival. Fortunately, textile materials are entering the warehouse one after another, while high-efficiency filter materials are in short supply. They ordered 5 tons of HEPA filter material from a supplier in Dalian years ago.

On January 29(the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, the second day of the resumption of work) , Wang Yi began to urge the goods, the other side said, now the goods are not easy to send, you no longer order 10 tons of viscose cloth, then 15 tons together delivery is easier.

Wang Yi then put 10 tons of viscose cloth all the money to the other side. February 3, Wang Yi again urge goods, the other side said it is difficult to ship. They are owned by medical device assets, all of which are supervised by local governments and primarily supplied locally. "If the Xiantao government contacts and communicates with the Dalian government, then we can get explicit regulations from the Dalian government so that we can arrange the production of filter paper outside the city as soon as possible. "

"But there is another way, " he added. "You can give us masks for free. We don't use them for ourselves. We donate them to the Dalian government so we can arrange production earlier. ".

"It's like a vicious circle, " Wang said. "manufacturers of raw materials are adding additional conditions because of a shortage of masks. They use masks to get support from local governments, but they don't want to supply raw materials. How can they produce masks without raw materials? ".

Wang Yi's company has a daily production capacity of one million birds per day. Three million were produced in four days. After the shutdown, a number of downstream business demand for goods, Wang Yi is very helpless, can only shoot empty factory told each other, "has stopped" , implied meaning is not to supply, but really no goods.

Several small and medium-sized enterprises mask business said, we closed a few days ago, mainly for fear of staff infection, can not bear responsibility. Our own production capacity is also relatively small, each day is only 200,000, not enough for a customer's volume, not to please. We're GONNA shut it down early.

"wants the government to guide manufacturers. "

Xiantao civil mask production capacity, but also brought a series of sequelae.

"medical (mask) is not allowed to sell, civilian masks are not allowed to do, more can not buy masks, mask prices from 50 cents to a piece, from a piece to two pieces, only a few days. ". Wang Yi poured out his bitterness.

According to several Xiantao mask manufacturers, masks are simply not available on the market. A mask costs 1.60 yuan, or even 2 yuan, which is unimaginably high. Under normal circumstances, the factory price of a mask is only a few cents.

Netease Qingliu studio for the purchase of masks to call Xiantao Changxing Plastic Products Co. , Ltd. Xiachabu branch of an employee phone, the other side said that the current price of 2 yuan / only, very expensive, do you want? If transportation is required, an additional charge of 30 cents per unit will be levied.

"We hope that the government can set a unified price and set a ceiling on the retail price and market price, which will help guide manufacturers to increase production, otherwise the price hype will go off the rails and the market will become more chaotic, and this is not the time to make a fortune, " Wang said.

Many mask manufacturers said that the current outbreak of high tension, hope that local governments can guide the production of micro, small and medium enterprises rather than a blanket closure. From the production point of view, although the civilian mask is not as high as the medical mask requirements, but in the civilian field, if the civilian mask also uses high-efficiency filter material, can play the same protective effect as the medical mask. In the case of high resource scarcity, the government has encouraged the civilian mask manufacturers to process production, and even can be stationed in the factory to monitor production.

Liu Pei is a senior writer at Qingliu Studio, based in Beijing.
